docs.lead_paragraph: EGYPT, one gathers in Israel, is a land of shocking contrasts between the rich few and the multitudinous poor, and the assumption is made that such a condition makes any Cairo regime intrinsically unstable. The present military leaders are appraised as honest, patriotic and idealistic, but often misguided. Their efforts to better the fellahin's lot are reported in Israel to be producing small results. Consequently, it is thought the poor are dissatisfied.

headline.main: A newcomer says Egypt is not so big and back-word as Israel believes.; Egypt: Myths And Realities

docs.abstract: contrast actual conditions with misconceptions each country has of the other
